      "message": "Hi,\n\nI worked with Ed, James Feist, and Gunnar Mills to define those two association types about 5 years ago.\n\nThey are documented here: https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/architecture/sensor-architecture.md\n\nThey were reviewed here: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/docs/+/22976\n\nWe needed two types of associations:\n* One from a chassis to all of its sensors so we could respond properly to Redfish URIs like /redfish/v1/Chassis/{ChassisId}/Sensors\n* One from a low inventory item to its sensors so we could get VPD, health status, etc.\n\nFor example, a fan or PSU sensor is associated with a low level mechanical fan or PSU with VPD and health status.  It is also associated with the higher level chassis (sled, drawer, etc.) so that /redfish/v1/Chassis/{ChassisId}/Sensors will work.\n\nThe \"inventory\" \u003c-\u003e \"sensors\" association is used in bmcweb here: https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/master/redfish-core/lib/sensors.hpp#L1140\n\nThese two association types are defined in associations JSON files but are also implemented in C++ code such as the phosphor-voltage-regulators application.  Removing the \"inventory\" \u003c-\u003e \"sensors\" association would require changing several upstream applications and would break current behavior in bmcweb.",
      "parentUuid": "5691c00c_d25fd2bc",
